title._content: Photograph of the Naval hockey team

description._content:
This image comes from a photographic album consisting of forty-five pages that was compiled by Petty Officer Harry Owen Hamment who served with the RAN for six years from 1952. The albums contain photographs and postcards pasted on each page. The postcards were collected in Singapore, Hong Kong, Japan and Korea between November 1953 and June 1954. 

The Australian National Maritime Museum undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. If you can identify a person, vessel or landmark, write the details in the Comments box below. 

Thank you for helping caption this important historical image.

Object number ANMS1337[003]
